LIC END--><br><br>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-<br>MacLear,<br><br>I thank you all for the help to find the cure for the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showMessage?topicID=1383.topic">blindness curse on our guards</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. The raid on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showMessage?topicID=1392.topic">Blackburrow</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> was successful but I once again need your help in retrieving some items from Najena. <br><br>Our primary target will be the Giant Black Widows, we need their silks. <br><br>I call upon all MacLear that are above their 15th season to join us. I hope that the powerful Geodon will join us for we will need his majiks to bring us to the land called <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/lavastorm.html">Lavastorm Mountains</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. This task will not be easy but I am sure that if enough of MacLear join us, we will have little difficulty.<br><br>I urge all that plan on helping to go to the library and read about the undead minions in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/najena.html">Najena</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and to look at the maps also.<br><br>Please send me a message if you can attend for all help is needed. I am plan on doing this Sunday eve (8:30pm EST - 17 Feb 2002)<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.graphicomm.com/~spikep/brut.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The Ranger walks back to his room hoping that he will get the support he needs</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ubrutredblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutredblade</A> at: 2/11/02 7:40:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=agravainebyremore>Agravaine Byremore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 635<br> <font color=#330000>(2/11/02 8:16:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1400.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The journey to Najena</span><hr size=1> Think I can probably make this event.<br><br>Agra <p><img src="//home.attbi.com/~geist22/agravaine.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulanadena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lanadena</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chief of Norrath</span><br>  Posts: 1012<br> <font color=#330000>(2/12/02 3:30:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1400.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The journey to Najena</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Lanadena reads Brut's scroll and pens a reply of her own.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>Brother Brut,<br><br>I apologize for flying into a rage the evening of the mishap.  I know that when one consorts with Teir'Dals at a young age it can twist one's mind.  If nothing else, the ties that bind you, whether they be friendship or hatred can always come back to haunt you or put you in a compromising position.  I know of what I speak from personal experience.  However, any doubts I had about you have been pushed completely away.<br><br>It would be my honor to fight alongside you to help the McMarrin Brothers.  Expect my presence with you in Najena.  If the cure is not found soon, I am afraid the blindness may be permanent.  <br><br>Cloven is sorrowful at the state he and his brothers have found themselves.  He holds some guilt that his love for Blackburrow Stout caused this tragedy.  He has sworn not to drink a drop of alcohol until he is cured.  And he further swears that he will only drink MacLear brewed items after that.  I suppose that means Raevenheart will have a regular customer but no words have brought Cloven comfort.  It tears my heart to see a Northman suffer so.<br><br>Lanadena <br> <p><a href="//home.attbi.com/~geist22/lanadena2.jpg"><center><img src="//home.attbi.com/~geist22/lanadena2.jpg" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ravnanger>Ravnanger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Shaman and Noble</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#330000>(2/12/02 6:49:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1400.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The journey to Najena</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> A Large ghost white dire wolf slowly pads out of the shadows. For a moment he pauses and takes a bearing. Looking around at the dias in the center of the room he startles as it flashes depositing people in the spells wake. The wolfs Glacier blue eyes flash with a reflection of Magical light. He turns and lopes down a corridor towards a busy market place filled with people.<br><br><br>Ravnanger closes a transaction with the banker and turns to leave. His vision whitens and eyes water. Before him stands the wolf. The many voices of the Bazzar are gone and only distant howl of wind can be heard. Meeting the wolfs gaze, Ravnanger recieves a message and a story. He nods and leans down to the wolf, whispering to the wolf and placing a bit of Imbued Ivory in its mouth. Ivory etched  with a shamans magic,to tell Brutredblade he will be there.  The wolf fades away, his vision returns.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br><br> <p><ahref="home.attbi.com/~geist22/ravnanger.jpg"><center><img src="//home.attbi.com/~geist22/ravnanger.jpg"border="0"></a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uraevenheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raevenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(2/13/02 8:55:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1400.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The journey to Najena</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The wind blew through the leaves carrying a message from Ravnanger, the MacLear High Shaman &quot;Druid...Ye are needed...&quot;  Raevenheart pulled up his roots, upsetting the squirrel that had endeavored to make a home there... and throught the mad chatter of the creature set out for his home...Halas, leaving in his path summoned acorns for the little critter he just upset.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>Butredblade, I shall try to be there...<br>Raevenheart <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=1400.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fthe